<article id="post-1490" class="post-1490 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-bhikkhus-notebook category-dhamma-article">
			<header class="entry-header">
			<h1 class="entry-title">Resistance and Designation (Notes on DN 15)</h1>		</header><!-- .entry-header -->		<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="byline">
				<a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/author/nyanamoli/" title="Posts by Bhikkhu Ninoslav Nyanamoli" rel="author">Bhikkhu Ninoslav Nyanamoli</a>			</span>
							<span class="cat-links">
					<a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/category/bhikkhus-notebook/" rel="category tag">Bhikkhu's Notebook</a>, <a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/category/dhamma-article/" rel="category tag">Dhamma Article</a>				</span><!-- .cat-links -->
			
			
			<span class="published-on">
				<time class="entry-date published" datetime="2013-03-28T16:37:08+00:00">March 28, 2013</time><time class="updated" datetime="2013-05-14T17:55:55+00:00">May 14, 2013</time>			</span>

			<span class="word-count">8 Minutes</span>		</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p data-adtags-visited="true">&nbsp;</p>
<p data-adtags-visited="true"><a href="https://pathpress.files.wordpress.com/2013/03/resistance_and_designation_nyanamoli.pdf"><img data-attachment-id="1022" data-permalink="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2010/08/14/hierarchy-of-awareness/pdf-download/" data-orig-file="https://pathpress.files.wordpress.com/2010/12/pdf-download.gif" data-orig-size="42,42" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;}" data-image-title="pdf-download" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://pathpress.files.wordpress.com/2010/12/pdf-download.gif?w=42" data-large-file="https://pathpress.files.wordpress.com/2010/12/pdf-download.gif?w=42" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1022" title="pdf-download" alt="" src="https://pathpress.files.wordpress.com/2010/12/pdf-download.gif?w=42" width="42" height="42" src-orig="https://pathpress.files.wordpress.com/2010/12/pdf-download.gif?w=1100" scale="2"></a></p>
<p style="padding-left:90px;" data-adtags-visited="true"><em>N─ümar┼½papaccay─ü phassoŌĆÖti iti kho panetaß╣ā vuttaß╣ā, tad─ünanda,</em><br>
<em> imin─üpetaß╣ā pariy─üyena veditabbaß╣ā, yath─ü n─ümar┼½papaccay─ü phasso. Yehi,</em><br>
<em> ─Ćnanda, ─ük─ürehi yehi liß╣ģgehi yehi nimittehi yehi uddesehi n─ümak─ü-yassa</em><br>
<em> pa├▒├▒atti hoti, tesu ─ük─üresu tesu liß╣ģgesu tesu nimittesu tesu uddesesu</em><br>
<em> asati api nu kho r┼½pak─üye adhivacanasamphasso pa├▒├▒─üyeth─ü ti?<span id="more-1490"></span></em></p>
<p style="padding-left:90px;" data-adtags-visited="true"><em>No hetaß╣ā, bhante.</em></p>
<p style="padding-left:90px;" data-adtags-visited="true"><em>Yehi, ─Ćnanda, ─ük─ürehi yehi liß╣ģgehi yehi nimittehi yehi uddesehi</em><br>
<em> r┼½pak─üyassa pa├▒├▒atti hoti, tesu ─ük─üresu tesu ─ük─üresu tesu liß╣ģgesu</em><br>
<em> tesu nimittesu tesu uddesesu tesu uddesesu asati, api nu kho n─ümak─üye</em><br>
<em> paß╣Łighasamphasso pa├▒├▒─üyeth─ü ti?</em></p>
<p style="padding-left:90px;" data-adtags-visited="true"><em>No hetaß╣ā, bhante.</em></p>
<p class="inline-ad-slot" id="inline-ad-0" style="float:left;height:0px;margin:0 auto;overflow:hidden;width:349px;" data-adtags-width="349" data-adtags-visited="true"></p><p style="padding-left:90px;" data-adtags-visited="true"><em>Yehi, ─Ćnanda, ─ük─ürehi yehi liß╣ģgehi yehi nimittehi yehi uddesehi</em><br>
<em> n─ümak─üyassa ca r┼½pak─üyassa ca pa├▒├▒atti hoti, tesu ─ük─üresu tesu ─ük─üresu</em><br>
<em> tesu liß╣ģgesu tesu nimittesu tesu uddesesu tesu uddesesu asati, api</em><br>
<em> nu kho adhivacanasamphasso v─ü paß╣Łighasamphasso v─ü pa├▒├▒─üyeth─ü ti?</em></p>
<p style="padding-left:90px;"><em>No hetaß╣ā, bhante.</em></p>
<p style="padding-left:90px;"><em>Yehi, ─Ćnanda, ─ük─ürehi yehi liß╣ģgehi yehi nimittehi yehi uddesehi</em><br>
<em> n─üma-r┼½passa pa├▒├▒atti hoti, tesu ─ük─üresu tesu ─ük─üresu tesu liß╣ģgesu</em><br>
<em> tesu nimittesu tesu uddesesu tesu uddesesu asati, api nu kho phasso</em><br>
<em> pa├▒├▒─ü-yeth─ü ti?</em></p>
<p style="padding-left:90px;"><em>No hetaß╣ā, bhante.</em></p>
<p style="padding-left:90px;"><em>Tasm─ütih─ünanda, eseva hetu etaß╣ā nid─ünaß╣ā esa samudayo esa paccayo</em><br>
<em> phassassa, yadidaß╣ā n─ümar┼½paß╣ā.</em></p>
<p style="padding-left:90px;">-ŌĆśWith name-&amp;-matter as condition, contactŌĆÖ, so it was said: how<br>
it is, ─Ćnanda, that with name-&amp;-matter as condition there is contact<br>
should be seen in this manner. Those tokens, ─Ćnanda, those marks,<br>
those signs, those indications by which the name-body is described,ŌĆöthey<br>
being absent, would designation-contact be manifest in the matter-body?</p>
<p style="text-align:left;padding-left:90px;">-No indeed, lord.</p>
<p style="padding-left:90px;">-Those tokens, ─Ćnanda, those marks, those signs, those indications<br>
by which the matter-body is described,ŌĆöthey being absent, would resistance-contact<br>
be manifest in the name-body?</p>
<p style="padding-left:90px;">-No indeed, lord.</p>
<p style="padding-left:90px;">-Those tokens, ─Ćnanda, those marks, those signs, those indications<br>
by which the name-body and the matter-body are described,ŌĆöthey being<br>
absent, would either designation-contact or resistance-contact be<br>
manifest?</p>
<p style="padding-left:90px;">-No indeed, lord.</p>
<p style="padding-left:90px;">-Those tokens, ─Ćnanda, those marks, those signs, those indications<br>
by which name-&amp;-matter is described,ŌĆöthey being absent, would contact<br>
be manifest?</p>
<p style="padding-left:90px;">-No indeed, lord.</p>
<p style="padding-left:90px;">-Therefore, ─Ćnanda, just this is the reason, this is the occasion,<br>
this is the arising, this is the condition of contact, that is to<br>
say name-&amp;-matter.<a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#f1"><br>
</a></p>
<p style="padding-left:60px;"><!--more--></p>
<p>1. ŌĆśMatterŌĆÖ is required for ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ to be present. If there would not be that which is ŌĆśnamedŌĆÖ, ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ would not be able to arise. If on the other hand, ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ is absent, ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ would simply be inconceivable. Thus, there is no ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ without ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ and there is no ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ without ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ, hence-<em>name-&amp;-matter</em>. In this way ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ <em>designates</em> the resistance, and ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ <em>resists </em>the designation. Without ŌĆśname'(-body), there would not be any designation manifested in ŌĆśmatter'(-body), but without ŌĆśmatter'(-body), there would not be any resistance manifested in the ŌĆśname'(-body). It is these respective <em>manifestations</em> of ŌĆśdesignationŌĆÖ and ŌĆśresistanceŌĆÖ that are <em>puthujjanaŌĆÖs</em> problem.</p>
<p>2. With name-&amp;-matter, he <em>assumes</em> that it is <em>this</em> ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ that is <em>designated.</em> Through that <em>assumption,</em> designation <em>manifests</em> in that matter body<a id="tthFrefAAB" href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFtNtAAB"><sup>1</sup></a>. In this way oneŌĆÖs ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ is <em>designated</em>-one is <em>contacted</em>.</p>
<p>With name-&amp;-matter, he <em>assumes</em> that it is <em>this</em> ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ that is <em>resisted.</em> Through that <em>assumption,</em> resistance <em>manifests</em> in that name-body. In this way oneŌĆÖs ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ is <em>resisted</em>-one is <em>contacted</em>.</p>
<p style="padding-left:30px;"><span style="text-decoration:underline;">He assumes that it is <em>this</em> ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ that is designated.</span><br>
He assumes it is the <em>same</em> ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ that is designated and is the condition for ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ; he assumes it is a <em>different </em>ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ that is designated and is the condition for ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ; He assumes it is <em>both-same-&amp;-different</em> matter that is designated and is the condition for ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ; He assumes it is <em>neither-same-nor-different</em> ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ that is designated and is the condition for ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ. Either way-the assumption<em> </em>is <em>there.</em></p>
<p style="padding-left:30px;">That which resists him he designates as the same, different, both-same-&amp;-different, or neither same-nor-different, as that because of which ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ is there. The designation <em>manifests </em>in this ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ.<a id="tthFrefAAC" href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFtNtAAC"><sup>2</sup></a><br>
Thus, he designates (<em>contacts</em>) his resistance. Contact is there.</p>
<p style="padding-left:30px;"><span style="text-decoration:underline;">He assumes that it is <em>this</em> ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ that is resisted.</span><br>
He assumes it is the <em>same</em> ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ that is resisted and is the condition for ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ; He assumes it is a <em>different</em> ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ that is resisted and is the condition for ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ; He assumes it is <em>both-same-&amp;-different</em> ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ that is resisted and is the condition for ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ; He assumes it is <em>neither-same-nor-different</em> ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ that is resisted and is the condition for ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ; Either way-the assumption<em> </em>is <em>there.</em></p>
<p style="padding-left:30px;">That which is designated he resists as the same, different, both-same-&amp;-different, or neither same-nor-different, as that because of which ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ is there. The resistance <em>manifests</em> in this ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ.<a id="tthFrefAAD" href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFtNtAAD"><sup>3</sup></a><br>
Thus, he resists (<em>contacts</em>) his designation. Contact is there.</p>
<p>3. <em>Cf. M┼½ßĖĘapariy─üya Sutta</em>, MN 1:</p>
<p><em>Pathaviß╣ā pathavito sa├▒j─ün─üti; pathaviß╣ā pathavito sa├▒├▒atv─ü pathaviß╣ā ma├▒├▒ati, pathaviy─ü ma├▒├▒ati, pathavito ma├▒├▒ati, pathaviß╣ā meti ma├▒├▒ati, pathaviß╣ā abhinandati. taß╣ā kissa hetu? `apari├▒├▒─ütaß╣ā tass─üŌĆÖti vad─ümi.</em></p>
<p>From earth, he has a percept of earth; having had from earth a percept, he conceives [that to be] earth, he conceives [that to be] in earth, he conceives [that to be] out of earth, he conceives earth as ŌĆśmineŌĆÖ, he delights earth. Why is that? He has not fully understood it, I sayŌĆ”</p>
<p>What a <em>puthujjana </em>has to realise is that regardless of <em>what</em> he perceives, it is always his <em>perception </em>that is perceived. Whether it is ŌĆśearthŌĆÖ, ŌĆśwaterŌĆÖ, ŌĆśfireŌĆÖ, ŌĆśairŌĆÖ or any other thing that MN 1 mentions, all one will ever perceive (<em>puthujjana</em> and <em>arahant</em> alike) is oneŌĆÖs own perception of that ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ.<a id="tthFrefAAE" href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFtNtAAE"><sup>4</sup></a> This is saying nothing else than ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ is and will <em>always be outside</em> of oneŌĆÖs reach, outside of that which has appeared.<a id="tthFrefAAF" href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFtNtAAF"><sup>5</sup></a> Perception is that which is perceived, but perception would not be possible if there is no matter to be perceived; on the other hand matter would be <em>inconceivable</em> if perception was indiscernible. If one thinks ŌĆ£it is because of the matter, that perception is thereŌĆØ, <em>that</em> thought is <em>perceived</em>, which means that <em>that</em> which is ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ <em>in that thought</em> is also perceived. But since it is only perception that can be perceived, that ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ which is perceived in that thought, cannot be that ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ which cannot be perceived, since it is perceived. In this way, <em>from</em> ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ, a <em>puthujjana</em> has a percept of ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ, which he <em>conceives </em>to be that <em>same</em> ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ because of which there is a percept of matter. Or he conceives it to be <em>different </em>ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ because of which there is a percept of matter. Or he conceives it to be <em>both-same &amp;-different </em>ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ because of which there is a percept of matter. Or he conceives it to be <em>neither-same-nor-different</em> ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ because of which there is a percept of matter. Either way ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ is <em>conceived.</em> He becomes responsible for the <em>manifestation</em> of the conceiving of that ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ, he ŌĆ£makesŌĆØ that ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ <em>exist</em>.<a id="tthFrefAAG" href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFtNtAAG"><sup>6</sup></a> That ŌĆ£creationŌĆØ is <em>his-</em>thus it is ŌĆś<em>my</em>ŌĆś ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ.<a id="tthFrefAAH" href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFtNtAAH"><sup>7</sup></a> But, since that ŌĆśmy matterŌĆÖ is conceived as that ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ <em>because of which </em>there is a percept of matter, then that percept[ion]<br>
too becomes ŌĆś<em>my perceptionŌĆÖ.</em><a id="tthFrefAAI" href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFtNtAAI"><sup>8</sup></a><em> </em>The same goes for oneŌĆÖs feelings and intentions. They are all conceived as <em>mine</em>. Since the <em>puthujjanaŌĆÖs</em> whole experience is <em>his</em>, he thinks he <em>himself</em> <em>is-</em>the view of Self exists.<a id="tthFrefAAJ" href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFtNtAAJ"><sup>9</sup></a></p>
<p>4. When consciousness does not indicate any ŌĆśmeŌĆÖ or ŌĆśmineŌĆÖ, that ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ because of which there is a percept of matter, does not manifest itself in that perception (or feeling, or intention)-it does not manifest itself in ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ. Thus, in perception there is only perception, i.e. in the seen there is only that which is seen, namely-the seen (and so on for all the senses).<a id="tthFrefABA" href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFtNtABA"><sup>10</sup></a> One ceases to ŌĆ£perceive ŌĆśmatterŌĆØŌĆś; one <em>knows</em><a id="tthFrefABB" href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFtNtABB"><sup>11</sup></a> such a thing is impossible or <em>inconceivable</em>,<a id="tthFrefABC" href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFtNtABC"><sup>12</sup></a> one simply <em>understands</em><a id="tthFrefABD" href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFtNtABD"><sup>13</sup></a>: <em>there is</em> matter, <em>there is </em>perception (or feeling, or intention), <em>there is </em>(non-indicative) consciousness. One <em>understands-</em>there are five ŌĆ£heapsŌĆØ.<a id="tthFrefABE" href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFtNtABE"><sup>14</sup></a> Since one understands them, one ceases to <em>assume </em>them. With the cessation of assumption, <em>that </em>which they were <em>assumed to be</em>, ceases-<em>bhava</em> comes to an end.</p>
<p style="text-align:right;">Bhikkhu Ninoslav ├æ─üß╣ćamoli</p>
<hr>
<h3>Footnotes:</h3>
<div class="p"></div>
<p><a id="tthFtNtAAB"></a><a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFrefAAB"><sup>1</sup></a><em>up─üd─ünapaccay─ü bhavo.</em></p>
<div class="p"></div>
<p><a id="tthFtNtAAC"></a><a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFrefAAC"><sup>2</sup></a>ŌĆśNameŌĆÖ <em>assumes existence </em>in ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ-ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ <em>exists</em>.</p>
<div class="p"></div>
<p><a id="tthFtNtAAD"></a><a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFrefAAD"><sup>3</sup></a>ŌĆśMatterŌĆÖ <em>finds footing </em>in ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ-ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ <em>exists</em>.<em>Cf. </em>DN 11.</p>
<div class="p"></div>
<p><a id="tthFtNtAAE"></a><a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFrefAAE"><sup>4</sup></a></p>
<blockquote>
<div>It would be as wrong to say ŌĆśa feeling is perceivedŌĆÖ as it would ŌĆśa percept is feltŌĆÖ (which mix up <em>sa├▒├▒─ü</em> and <em>vedan─ü</em>); but it is quite in order to say ŌĆśa feeling, a percept, (that is, a felt thing, a perceived thing) is cognizedŌĆÖ, which simply means that a feeling or a percept is present (as, indeed, they both are in all experienceŌĆösee <em>Majjhima</em> v,3 (M.i,293)). Strictly speaking, then, what is <em>cognized</em> is <em>n─ümar┼½pa</em>, whereas what is <em>perceived</em> (or <em>felt</em>) is <em>sa├▒├▒─ü</em> (or <em>vedan─ü</em>), i.e. only <em>n─üma</em>. This distinction can be shown grammatically. <em>Vij─ün─üti</em>, to cognize, is active voice in sense (taking an objective accusative): consciousness <em>cognizes a phenomenon</em> (<em>n─ümar┼½pa</em>); consciousness is always consciousness <em>of</em> something. <em>Sa├▒j─ün─üti</em>, to perceive, (or <em>vediyati</em>, to feel) is middle voice in sense (taking a cognate accusative): perception <em>perceives</em> [a percept] (or feeling feels [a feeling]). Thus we should say ŌĆśa blue thing (= a blueness), a painful thing (= a pain), is cognizedŌĆÖ, but ŌĆśblue is perceivedŌĆÖ and ŌĆśpain is feltŌĆÖ. (In the Suttas generally, due allowance is to be made for the elasticity in the common usage of words. But in certain passages, and also in oneŌĆÖs finer thinking, stricter definition may be required.)-├æ─üß╣ćav─½ra Thera, <em>Clearing the Path</em>, 2010, p. 92.</div>
</blockquote>
<div class="p"></div>
<p><a id="tthFtNtAAF"></a><a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFrefAAF"><sup>5</sup></a><em>Cf.</em> ├æ─üß╣ćav─½ra Thera, <em>Seeking The Path, </em>2010, p. 40, ┬¦┬¦17-18: ŌĆ£[Four <em>mah─übhut─ü</em>]ŌĆ”will always be just below our feet.ŌĆØ</p>
<div class="p"></div>
<p><a id="tthFtNtAAG"></a><a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFrefAAG"><sup>6</sup></a>Thus, ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ<em> </em>can never be perceived, but it can ŌĆ£find footingŌĆØ in that which is perceived (or felt, or intended).</p>
<div class="p"></div>
<p><a id="tthFtNtAAH"></a><a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFrefAAH"><sup>7</sup></a>He delights in his own creation, <em>because </em>it is his own creation.</p>
<div class="p"></div>
<p><a id="tthFtNtAAI"></a><a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFrefAAI"><sup>8</sup></a>If one is not to conceive that ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ <em>because of which</em> there is a percept of matter, one would not <em>conceive oneself</em> as <em>that because of which</em> there is a perceiver and conceiver of the world. <em>Cf. </em>SN 35.116:</p>
<blockquote>
<div>The eyeŌĆ” earŌĆ” noseŌĆ” tongueŌĆ” bodyŌĆ” mindŌĆ” is that in the<br>
world <em>by which </em>one is a perceiver and conceiver of the world.</div>
</blockquote>
<p>Also,<em> cf. </em>├æ─üß╣ćav─½ra Thera, <em><span class="skimlinks-unlinked">op.cit</span>. </em>p. 298:</p>
<blockquote>
<div>And <em>when</em> shall we ŌĆśnot be that by whichŌĆÖ? ŌĆ” the Buddha tells us: it is when, for us, in the seen there shall be just the seen, and so with the heard, the sensed, and the cognized. And when in the seen is there just the seen? When the seen is no longer seen as ŌĆśmineŌĆÖ (<em>etaß╣ā mama</em>) or as ŌĆśIŌĆÖ (<em>esoŌĆÖham asmi</em>) or as ŌĆśmy selfŌĆÖ (<em>eso me att─ü</em>): in brief, when there is no longer, in connexion with the senses, the conceit ŌĆśI amŌĆÖ, <em>by which</em> ŌĆśI am a conceiver of the worldŌĆÖ.</div>
</blockquote>
<div class="p"></div>
<p><a id="tthFtNtAAJ"></a><a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFrefAAJ"><sup>9</sup></a>ThatŌĆÖs how the sense of the ŌĆśmineŌĆÖ leads to the sense of ŌĆśSelfŌĆÖ.</p>
<div class="p"></div>
<p><a id="tthFtNtABA"></a><a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFrefABA"><sup>10</sup></a><em>Cf. B─ühiya Sutta</em>, Ud. 10/8.</p>
<div class="p"></div>
<p><a id="tthFtNtABB"></a><a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFrefABB"><sup>11</sup></a>ŌĆ£Wisdom is to be developedŌĆ”ŌĆØ-MN 43.</p>
<div class="p"></div>
<p><a id="tthFtNtABC"></a><a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFrefABC"><sup>12</sup></a>If it were fundamentally subject to oneŌĆÖs conceivings, freedom from conceivings would not be possible. <em>Cf. </em>my <a title="The Infinity of The Mind (Notes on AN&nbsp;1.51)" href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/19/the-infinity-of-the-mind-notes-on-an-1-51/" target="_blank"><em>Notes on AN 1.51</em></a>.</p>
<div class="p"></div>
<p><a id="tthFtNtABD"></a><a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFrefABD"><sup>13</sup></a>ŌĆ£ŌĆ”consciousness is to be understoodŌĆØ.-MN 43.</p>
<div class="p"></div>
<p><a id="tthFtNtABE"></a><a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#tthFrefABE"><sup>14</sup></a>Simultaneous, superimposed, utterly <em>indifferent </em>to each other.</p>
