		<li id="comment-478" class="comment even depth-3 parent">
			<article id="div-comment-478" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt="" src="https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/bea78d5a4f802d8134b53260c6a95089?s=48&amp;d=https%3A%2F%2F2.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=G" class="avatar avatar-48" height="48" width="48">						<b class="fn">acha</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#comment-478"><time datetime="2013-05-03T11:00:29+00:00">May 3, 2013 at 11:00 am</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Thanks Bhikkhu,</p>
<p>I was not familiar with the sutta terminology that you refer to.<br>
I appreciate that your approach is based on ŌĆśpracticeŌĆÖ and is not concerned with a merely intellectual understanding.<br>
Your writings suggest that you are a person who can hold many different points of view in your mind ŌĆō alas, I am a person who needs things to be simple.<br>
Am I right therefore in thinking that all the various points we have discussed could be phrased in a modified version of what you wrote? ie. </p>
<p>He assumes that behaviour of this appearance is known as/from ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ</p>
<p>He assumes that appearance of this behaviour is known as/from ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ.</p>
<p>Regards,</p>
<p>Acha</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

							</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-481" class="comment byuser comment-author-nyanamoli bypostauthor odd alt depth-3">
			<article id="div-comment-481" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt="" src="https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/d6f82f2d8134c609884846b390e5934e?s=48&amp;d=https%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=G" class="avatar avatar-48" height="48" width="48">						<b class="fn">Bhikkhu Ninoslav Nyanamoli</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://pathpress.wordpress.com/2013/03/28/resistance-and-designation/#comment-481"><time datetime="2013-05-10T07:24:05+00:00">May 10, 2013 at 7:24 am</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Dear Acha, </p>
<p>You could say:</p>
<p>He assumes that behaviour of this appearance is that which is ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ.<br>
He assumes that appearance of this behaviour is that which is ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ.</p>
<p>He does not know that ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ and ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ can only be known as ŌĆśappearanceŌĆÖ and ŌĆśbehaviourŌĆÖ, hence he /assumes/ them to be that. With ŌĆśassumptionŌĆÖ, behaviour and appearance are /identified/ (or conceived) with ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ and ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ respectively, and then there are following directions that this identification (conceiving) can go: </p>
<p>behaviour (appearance) is the same as ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ (name),<br>
behaviour (appearance) is different from ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ (name),<br>
behaviour (appearance) is both-the-same-and-different from ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ (name),<br>
behaviour (appearance) is neither-the-same-nor-different from ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ (name).</p>
<p>So the whole thing reads:</p>
<p>He assumes that behaviour of this appearance is that which is [the same as] ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ.<br>
He assumes that behaviour of this appearance is that which is [different from] ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ.<br>
He assumes that behaviour of this appearance is that which is [both-the-same-and-different from] ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ.<br>
He assumes that behaviour of this appearance is that which is [neither-the-same-nor-different from] ŌĆśmatterŌĆÖ.</p>
<p>Either way, for him, it is this appearance that /behaves/.</p>
<p>He assumes that appearance of this behaviour is that which is [the same as] ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ.<br>
He assumes that appearance of this behaviour is that which is [different from] ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ.<br>
He assumes that appearance of this behaviour is that which is [both-the-same-and-different from] ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ.<br>
He assumes that appearance of this behaviour is that which is [neither-the-same-nor-different from] ŌĆśnameŌĆÖ.</p>
<p>Either way, for him, it is this behaviour that /appears/.</p>
<p>What needs to be seen is that it is the behaviour that behaves and the appearance that appears, and the identification, in any of the above possible ways, /cannot fundamentally make any difference at all/ŌĆöbehaviour will be behaving and appearance will be appearing, they cannot enter each othersŌĆÖ domainsŌĆöthe structure remains unaffected. Apart from the indifferent simultaneous presence of behaviour and appearance, there is no relationship between the two and that is the very reason why freedom from them both is possible. (Of course, until this is understood, that lack-of-understanding /will be/ the relationship between the two).</p>
<p>Let me know what you think.</p>
<p>With best wishes, </p>
<p>Nyanamoli</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

